<FIRST>r w PM-Bush-Quayle-APMeeting     04-06 0119</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Bush-Quayle-AP Meeting,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bush, Quayle To Address AP Publishers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush and Vice President Dan Quayle
are scheduled to address the annual meeting and luncheon of The
Associated Press in separate appearances in Chicago on April 24.
   AP Chairman William J. Keating announced the appearances by the
president and the vice president at opening day events of the
American Newspaper Publishers Association annual convention.
   Never before have a president and a vice president addressed the
AP meetings on the same day.
   Some 2,000 AP member publishers and spouses are expected to
attend the two events. Bush will appear first at the annual meeting
of the news cooperative. Quayle will follow at the AP annual
luncheon.
</TEXT>
