Cat.'' Inside, upright-standing dogs, common characters in Larson's
wacky cartoons, are being served drinks by poodle waitresses and
listening to two dog musicians on stage.
   On the tables, a sign reads: ``Please keep table barking to a
minimum.'' A sign with a fireplug and an arrow hangs on one wall.
   Larson agreed to do the cover if Ellis offered to teach him a
few tricks of the trade, said company spokeswoman Merrilee Trost.
The record company, 45 miles east of San Francisco, flew Larson to
Ellis' home in Fairfield Bay, Ark., where the two spent two weeks
playing together.
