negotiations with Congress seeking $22.3 billion in fiscal 1990
spending author for their department _ the initial $21.9 billion
sought by Reagan plus $441 million for the Budition to the $250 million
for merit schools and $100
million for magnets, Bush is proposing:
   _$25 millionor grants to urban schools that have the most
serious drug problems.
   _$25 million for federal grants to develop ways to get
professionals from other fields into teachingstrative
