<HEAD>Rain Soaks East Coast; Heat Bakes Southwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A cold front spread rain across the Eastern Seaboard this
morning and a heat wave continued to grip much of California and
Arizona.
   Rain fell from New England to the mid-Atlantic states and
showers and thunderstorms were scattered across the Carolinas,
eastern Georgia and the Florida Peninsula.
   A heavy thunderstorm dumped an inch of rain in an hour at Cape
Hatteras, N.C., early this morning, a few hours after thunderstorm
winds gusting to 60 mph were recorded in the area. Newport News,
Va., received almost 1{ inches of rain in the six hours ended at 2
a.m. EDT.
   Showers also were scattered across the northern and central
Plains, the northern Rockies and parts of the northern Pacific
Coast.
   Clear skies were common across the Southwest.
   Early morning temperatures were still in the 60s and 70s across
much of California and Arizona. Eleven cities in the two states set
or tied record highs on Wednesday, including Los Angeles, where the
high of 105 was 15 degrees above the previous mark set in 1971.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms in the
mid-Atlantic coastal region and New England; scattered showers in
the middle and upper Mississippi Valley; rain and snow in the
Dakotas and the northern and central Rockies; and rain in
Washington state.
   Highs were expected to be in the 40s from northern Montana
across the northern Plains, upper Mississippi Valley, Great Lakes,
northern and central Appalachians to northern New England; 30s in
northern Michigan; 70s and 80s from Florida across the central Gulf
Coast, southern and central Plains, New Mexico, northern Arizona,
Utah, Nevada and from central California to Oregon; 90s to around
105 degrees in southern portions of Arizona and California.
   Elsewhere, highs were expected to be in the 50s and 60s.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 22 degrees at Warroad,
Minn., to 80 degrees at Glendale Luke Air Force Base, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 48 fair; Boston 51 rain; Buffalo 38 partly
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 61 cloudy; Cincinnati 40 cloudy; Cleveland
40 partly cloudy; Detroit 35 fair; Miami 68 cloudy; New York 51
rain; Philadelphia 51 rain; Pittsburgh 39 partly cloudy; Portland,
Maine 42 rain; Washington 51 rain.
