Pace, where they lived with Nicholson's family until Kimberly's
death.
   Before pleading guilty, Jackson testified that Nicholson cast a
religious trance over her, may have drugged her, and convinced her
that Kimberly was possessed.
   Jackson said Nicholson told her the spirits could be exorcised
only through fasting and punishment. Kimberly died after being
taken by ambulance from Nicholson's home to Santa Rosa Medical
Center.
   Nicholson was jailed in lieu of $250,000 bond following her
arrest Tuesday.
