<HEAD>Congressmen, Members of Parliament Will Volley to Aid Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Members of Congress and the British Parliament
will square off on a Washington area tennis court May 19 for the
benefit of Children's Hospital National Medical Center.
   Plans for the benefit were announced today by Sen. John Breaux,
D-La., and John Hannam, a member of the House of Commons, both of
whom will take part in the match and have been rounding up
colleagues to join them.
