<FIRST>r i AM-Germany-Truck     04-06 0152</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Germany-Truck,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Army Missile Truck Hits House After Brakes Fail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. Army truck carrying three
unarmed Hawk missiles crashed into a house on Thursday when the
vehicle's brakes failed, but no one was hurt, a military spokesman
said.
   Maj. David Hartman, spokesman for the 32nd Army Air Defense
Command in Darmstadt, said the crash occurred outside the rural
town of Weilerbach, about 55 miles southwest of Frankfurt, as the
truck was returning from a field exercise.
   He said the missiles were undamaged and the missile transporter,
a lengthened model of a 2{-ton truck, was towed to its home base
near Kaiserslautern.
   Hawks are ground-to-air rockets designed to carry a conventional
high-explosive warhead.
   The accident could set off new protests from West German peace
activists who complain that some ground and air maneuvers by NATO
forces based in West Germany put civilian lives at risk.
</TEXT>
