<FILEID>AP-NR-04-06-89 1415EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>s f BC-Mustang-Milestones Adv09   04-06 0364</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Mustang-Milestones, Adv 09,0381</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv09</HEAD>
<HEAD>For release Sunday, April 9</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Mustang Anniversary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are significant dates in the development and
marketing of Ford Motor Co.'s Mustang, celebrating its silver
anniversary this month:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Late 1960 _ Early work began in the development of a lightweight
sports car.
   Early 1962 _ Work got under way in earnest on the vehicle
designed to weigh less than 2,500 pounds and cost less than $2,500.
It went through a number of code names, including Allegro, Cougar
(no relation to the Mercury car) and T-5.
   March 9, 1964 _ Job One rolled off the line at Ford's Dearborn
assembly plant. It weighed 2,572 pounds with base sticker price of
$2,368.
   April 17, 1964 _ Formal introduction of the Mustang.
   April-August 1964 _ First-year sales projections of 100,000
Mustangs were surpassed in four months. More than 417,000 Mustangs
were sold during the first year of availability.
   Mid-1965 _ Ford added the GT-350 and GT-500 to the Mustang
stable, giving the car more power for the 1966 model year.
   1969 model year _ Mustang grew bulkier as ``muscle cars'' came
into vogue. During the next two model years, Ford introduced the
Mustang Mach I, Boss 302, Boss 429 and Boss 351.
   Mid-1970s _ The Arab oil embargo hit, and gasoline prices
soared, spelling trouble for high-powered, gas-gobbling cars.
   Mid-1973 _ Ford brought out the second generation of the car, a
smaller Mustang II, for the 1974 model year. During the next two
model years, the shell of the car remained virtually the same, but
Ford beefed up engines, offering a V-8 in 1975 and a Cobra II in
1976.
   Fall 1978 _ The third generation of the Mustang was introduced,
built on the same platform as Mercury Cougars and Ford Thunderbirds
of the day. The platform is used in the 1989 Mustang.
   Mid-1981 _ The Mustang GT was reintroduced.
   Fall 1985 _ Ford added a 5-liter high output engine, an option
the car still carries.
   April 1989 _ Ford quietly celebrates Mustang's Silver
Anniversary. A caravan of 37 Mustangs owned by Europeans begins
U.S. tour on the ``American Pony Drive.''
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End advance for Sunday, April 9</NOTE>
</DOC>
