<HEAD>London Shares Close Sharply Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout with closing prices.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices fell sharply Thursday on the London
Stock Exchange, depressed by program selling.
   The Financial Times 30 share index closed 21.2 points lower at
1,684.2. The FT-SE 100 index fell 25.7 points, or 1.23 percent, to
2,052.5. And the Financial Times 500 index closed down 14.37 at
1,167.84.
   Volume was 758.3 million shares, compared with 440.7 million
shares on Wednesday.
   Dealers said the market failed to gain any support from the
large financial institutions, which are holding back from buying
stock because of uncertainty about the outlook for the economy.
   Traders are concerned that any further weakness in sterling will
force the government to raise interest rates.
