<SECOND>BC-Training Pants,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kimberly Clark Announces New Disposable Training Pants</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kimberly Clark Corp. on Wednesday announced it
will begin making disposable training pants for toddlers, designed
for the 4 million children who annually outgrow their need for
diapers and begin toilet training.
   Darwin E. Smith, chairman and chief executive officer of
Kimberly Clark, said the product, which has been in development for
five years, will carry the name ``Huggies Pull-Ups.''
   ``They provide the absorption and protection of a disposable
diaper, but look like children's underwear and are worn like
underwear,'' Smith said.
   He said the pants will first be available in Arizona, Colorado
and parts of Wyoming, while distribution would be expanded when
production capacity permits.
   Kimberly Clark's Paris, Texas, plant was expanded by 300,000
feet to make room for new production lines to make the pants. Since
Jan. 1, the plant has added 135 workers to handle the new product.
